@@TJvSpecialFolder
<TITLE TJvSpecialFolder type>
Summary
  Defines the different special system folders available in Windows.
Description
  TJvSpecialFolder is the type for the <LINK TJvFindFilesDialog.SpecialFolder, SpecialFolder>
  property of the TJvFindFilesDialog component. It defines all allowable special folders on the
  system.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindFilesDialog.UseSpecialFolder
Summary
  Specifies what property is used for the root search folder.
Description
  Use UseSpecialFolder to specify whether the Directory or SpecialFolder property is used as the root
  folder for the search. Set this value to false to use Directory and to true to use SpecialFolder.
See Also
  TJvFindFilesDialog.Directory, TJvFindFilesDialog.SpecialFolder

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindFilesDialog.Execute
Summary
  Shows the search dialog.
Description
  Call Execute to display the search dialog.
Return value
  \True if the user didn't cancel the search.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindFilesDialog.SpecialFolder
Summary
  Specifies the start folder for the search.
Description
  Use SpecialFolder when you want to start a search in folders like Control Panel or Printers or a
  special folder that isn't a real file system folder.
See Also
  TJvFindFilesDialog.Directory

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvFindFilesDialog.Directory
Summary
  Specifies the start directory for the search.
Description
  Set Directory to the file system directory where the search should start. To start the search in a
  special folder (like Control Panel or \Printers), use the SpecialFolder property instead.
  Note
  The UseSpecialFolder property controls whether Directory or SpecialFolder is used as the start
  value.
See Also
  TJvFindFilesDialog.SpecialFolder

